  "body": "### Description\r\n\r\nWe have many \"common\"  libraries that we use in our Quarkus applications. Good practice is not to include the Quarkus runtimes in these libraries. e.g. if you want to upgrade the depending projects  on different timelines. \r\n\r\nHowever, some refactoring (making a common library) made me realize that when I include Panache, I get major parts from the Quarkus eco-system on my classpath. \r\n\r\nIs it possible to limit this just to an API? \r\n\r\nAnd, additionally, it would be nice if the Panache Unit test is not dependent on `@QuarkusTest` but on plain `@Test`. \r\n\r\n### Implementation ideas\r\n\r\n_No response_",
